86): Executes bind plugins until one successfully binds the pod\n- **RunPreFilterPlugins()** (line 709): Executes PreFilter plugins and returns PreFilterResult\n- **RunPostFilterPlugins()** (line 919): Executes PostFilter plugins for preemption handling\n- **RunPermitPlugins()** (line 1454): Executes Permit plugins to allow/wait/reject binding\n- **RunPreBindPlugins()**: Executes PreBind plugins before binding\n- **RunPostBindPlugins()**: Executes PostBind plugins after binding\n- **NewFramework()** (line 267): Factory function that creates a new Framework instance with a registry of plugins\n\n## Plugin Registry\n`pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/registry.go` defines:\n- **Registry** (line 71): A map[string]PluginFactory that holds all available plugins\n- **PluginFactory**: A function type for creating plugin instances\n- Registry methods: Register(), Unregister(), and Merge() for managing plugins\n\n## Built-in Plugin Registry\n`pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/registry.go` contains:\n- **NewInTreeRegistry()** (line 47): Factory function that builds the registry with all in-tree plugins including DefaultBinder, DynamicResources, ImageLocality, InterPodAffinity, NodeAffinity, NodeName, NodePorts, NodeResources, NodeUnschedulable, NodeVolumeLimit, PodTopologySpread, QueueSort, DefaultPreemption, SchedulingGates, TaintToleration, VolumeBinding, VolumeRestrictions, and VolumeZone\n\n## Top-level Scheduler Orchestration\n`pkg/scheduler/scheduler.go` contains:\n- **Scheduler** (line 66): The top-level struct that manages the scheduling workflow, containing Cache, Extenders, and Profiles\n- **Run()** (line 464): The main entry point that starts the scheduler's event loop and spawns a goroutine to repeatedly call ScheduleOne()\n\n## Scheduling Cycle Orchestration\n`pkg/scheduler/schedule_one.go` contains:\n- **ScheduleOne()** (line 65): The core function that orchestrates the entire scheduling workflow for a single pod, coordinating the framework plugin extensions to filter, score, reserve, permit, and bind pods\n\n## Supporting Data Structures\n`pkg/scheduler/framework/cycle_state.go`: Maintains state during a single scheduling cycle\n`pkg/scheduler/framework/types.go`: Defines core types like NodeScore, NodeInfo, and CycleState\n\nThe architecture follows a plugin-based design pattern where the frameworkImpl coordinates plugin execution at well-defined extension points throughout the scheduling cycle. Each plugin type (Filter, Score, Bind, etc.) represents a specific decision point in the scheduler's workflow."
